# Epic 4: Crop Recommendation and Prediction

## Overview

The Crop Recommendation module serves as the core component of the OptiCrop system. It analyzes soil nutrient values and environmental conditions to identify the most suitable crop for cultivation. The module applies a trained machine learning model to generate reliable predictions that support agricultural planning and decision-making.

---

## Purpose

The main purpose of this module is to assist users in selecting appropriate crops by evaluating agricultural parameters and providing intelligent recommendations.

---

## Required Inputs

The prediction model utilizes the following input values:

* Nitrogen (N)
* Phosphorus (P)
* Potassium (K)
* Temperature
* Humidity
* Soil pH
* Rainfall

These parameters represent the soil fertility and climatic conditions of the agricultural field.

---

## Prediction Workflow

The crop prediction process follows several stages:

1. The user provides soil and environmental information.
2. The system verifies the entered values.
3. The trained machine learning model is loaded into the application.
4. Input parameters are supplied to the model.
5. The model evaluates the data and predicts a crop category.
6. The prediction result is converted into the actual crop name.
7. The recommended crop is displayed to the user.

---

## Model Implementation

The system employs the Logistic Regression algorithm for crop classification. The trained model is saved and reused for prediction tasks, eliminating the need for repeated training.

Model storage allows the application to perform predictions efficiently and reduces computational overhead.

---

## Example Input

| Parameter   | Sample Value |
| ----------- | ------------ |
| Nitrogen    | 90           |
| Phosphorus  | 42           |
| Potassium   | 43           |
| Temperature | 20.8°C       |
| Humidity    | 82%          |
| pH          | 6.5          |
| Rainfall    | 202.9 mm     |

